'''Event Pokémon''' or '''costumed Pokémon''' are special forms that have appeared during various events for a limited time in {{g|GO}}.

These forms are usually an otherwise-normal Pokémon with an event-relevant costume. Some Event Pokémon can potentially be {{GO|Shiny Pokémon|Shiny}} as well, or know event-exclusive [[move]]s. Some Event Pokémon can evolve, and will retain their costume after doing so. From July 2021 until February 6, 2025, event forms (except [[Clone]] Pokémon) had their own category in the [[Pokédex]] of Pokémon GO. As of February 6, 2025, Event Pokémon, including Clone Pokémon, are shown as part of individual Pokémon entires within the standard Pokédex. Since Event Pokémon are unique to Pokémon GO, they cannot be transferred to {{LGPE}} and {{g|HOME}}. 

As of July 21, 2026, there are 309 Event Pokémon in total, originating from 124 species of Pokémon. This includes 64 costumed Pokémon released since the February 6, 2025 Pokédex update, 245 costumed Pokémon categorized in the deprecated Event Pokédex (243 unique costumes, and 2 duplicate costumes), 4 Clone Pokémon, and 6 variations in form (3 additional for {{p|Pumpkaboo}}, and 3 additional for {{p|Gourgeist}}).

==Terminology==
{{main|Terminology of Event Pokémon (GO)}}

In the dialogue of [[Pokémon GO]], these Pokémon are known as '''Event''', '''event''', '''special event''', '''costumed''', '''special costumed''', '''wearing costumes''', '''in costumes''', or '''sporting festive headwear''' (Japanese: '''{{ruby|着飾|きかざ}}った''' ''dressed-up'', '''{{ruby|帽子|ぼうし}}をかぶった''' ''hat-wearing'', '''{{ruby|特殊|とくしゅ}}''' ''special'', '''{{ruby|特別|とくべつ}}''' ''special'', or '''いつもとは違う''' ''other than usual'').

